    "bodyModel": {
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_0",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ed36",
          "text": "Preserving Science in Times of Collapse",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H3"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3f23",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*VRaxrrIyU9OZzYXhK5JcPw.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3d07",
          "text": "Yesterday I wrote an article about how the greatest threat to science is the impending collapse of our global economic system. This prompted many to ask how all of the scientific advances of the last 500 years might be preserved if indeed there is a catastrophic loss of social complexity at the planetary scale.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 125,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/the-threat-to-science-no-one-talks-about-c2d48ee13dd#.jm7h6nu1e",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 39,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8aa9",
          "text": "Should we create storehouses of books and pamphlets? Create digital archives of data and research findings? Hold onto the knowledge stores in the same way heirloom seeds are protected in a vault for post-collapse recovery?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 194,
              "href": "https://foodtank.com/news/2015/01/fifteen-seed-saving-initiatives-protecting-biodiversity-for-future-generati/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 155,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7acd",
          "text": "It matters that knowledge is embodied. As I have written about with respect to the technology “singularity”; how living systems attain intelligence through connectivity; and that we are on a living planet; the key insight to hold onto is that everything is connected and so we must think in terms of context and relationships.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 107,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/what-if-the-singularity-is-us-be5795cb42ae#.rn71392cn",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 83,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 168,
              "href": "https://medium.com/emergent-future/the-connective-intelligence-of-life-41f4b31a3ef#.1skorpr0j",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 135,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 204,
              "href": "https://medium.com/personal-growth/the-great-lie-of-living-on-a-dead-planet-d056d6de2c7d#.yjb62am4o",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 191,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 266,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 243,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 37,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 16,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "01ec",
          "text": "The same is true for preserving all of the advances of science and technology. We will not hold onto knowledge as disembodied storage of facts and figures. It will be necessary that we focus our attention on the social meshworks of people with body-based skills and training.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 275,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 228,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 212,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "cc10",
          "text": "This includes things like:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e721",
          "text": "Mentorship programs for skilled researchers to continue training new initiates to their fields.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fdc6",
          "text": "Institutional structures for managing communications and coordinating the necessary dialogue and debates that make science possible.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a8d7",
          "text": "Pooling of resources to hold space for these activities to take place.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "e948",
          "text": "Emphasis on social learning between all of the people involved, including how the learning process is structured and supported institutionally.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ba8d",
          "text": "In another recent essay, I described knowledge ecosystems in this way:",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 23,
              "href": "https://medium.com/age-of-awareness/the-look-and-feel-of-21st-century-science-443ffadc384#.7kbp2fs8r",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 11,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_12",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f83b",
          "text": "",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*Hu5A2TKN-mB1ZfEeqk7DXQ.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "6d56",
          "text": "What I meant by this is that learning systems in the future — including those for advancing the scientific method — will need to be treated as living systems. They will be made up of living human beings whose connectivity is configured in a manner that is resilient to societal collapse.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ea1e",
          "text": "This is a VERY tall order!",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a7e2",
          "text": "Yet it is what will be needed for us to avoid catastrophic setbacks. Avoiding another Dark Age will only be possible by thinking in human terms about social infrastructure. We need to move beyond the industrial factory metaphors for knowledge creation (e.g. productivity, efficiency, mass-production) and instead think in terms of ecosystems (e.g. human relationships, social capacities, various ways of thinking and doing).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 300,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 252,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 423,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 342,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "45a8",
          "text": "In my work as a Culture Designer, I keep coming back to the profound significance of embodiment. Human societies are only capable of navigating changes when they have the arrangements of leadership ethics, emotional intelligence, and trust in relationships to continue cooperating when under stress. Thus the need to focus on the human dimensions of science.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 358,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 300,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "dccb",
          "text": "I am early in this inquiry process. As I described yesterday, my life mission has transitioned from trying to avoid the worst of societal collapse (which I now deem unlikely being so late in the game) and into an effort to preserve all that is sacred through the collapse so that it remains available for future generations.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 60,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/the-threat-to-science-no-one-talks-about-c2d48ee13dd#.y9ytuww1b",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 41,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f7e5",
          "text": "You are invited to join me on this learning journey. How can we apply the tools of culture design to this level of problems? Will it be possible to grow a network of culture design labs around the world during the same period of collapse that now seems imminent? I don’t know the answers to these questions.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 97,
              "href": "http://www.slideshare.net/joebrewer31/tools-for-culture-design",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 74,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 185,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/a-global-network-of-culture-design-labs-7cf90746d58#.tmae9c89e",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 155,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "90e0",
          "text": "What I do know is that failure is not an option.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "2c7db3e2f3f8_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f40c",
          "text": "Onward, fellow humans.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
